<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="281" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,1126,1441]" pageId="16" pageNumber="281">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,287,1126,1152]" pageId="16" pageNumber="281">Comments.</emphasis>
This species was originally described under 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gauld &amp; Sithole" authorityYear="2002" box="[799,943,1127,1152]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Forrestopius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="281" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[799,943,1127,1152]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="281">Forrestopius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, it shows many features that disagree with the generic diagnosis, such as the palpal formula 4:3 (vs. 5: 
<quantity box="[958,1006,1162,1189]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.016" pageId="16" pageNumber="281" unit="in" value="4.0">4 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gauld &amp; Sithole" authorityYear="2002" box="[1014,1158,1163,1188]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Forrestopius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="281" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1014,1158,1163,1188]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="281">Forrestopius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); similar palpal formula can be also found in 
<taxonomicName authority="Gauld &amp; Sithole, 2002" authorityName="Gauld &amp; Sithole" authorityYear="2002" box="[382,804,1199,1225]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Leurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="281" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xalifer">
<emphasis box="[382,540,1199,1225]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="281">Leurus xalifer</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Gauld I. D. &amp; Sithole R. &amp; Subfamily Metopiinae &amp; In &amp; Gauld, I. D. &amp; Godoy, C. &amp; Ugalde Gomez, J. A." box="[547,804,1199,1225]" pageId="16" pageNumber="281" pagination="11 - 262" refId="ref11144" refString="Gauld I. D. &amp; Sithole R. (2002) Subfamily Metopiinae. In: Gauld, I. D., Godoy, C. &amp; Ugalde Gomez, J. A., The Ichneumonidae of Costa Rica 4. Memoirs of the American Entomological Institute, 66, pp. 11 - 262." type="journal article" year="2002">Gauld &amp; Sithole, 2002</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Alvarado &amp; Palacio" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Gauld &amp; Sithole" baseAuthorityYear="2002" box="[813,962,1199,1225]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Leurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="281" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="larryi">
<emphasis box="[813,962,1199,1225]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="281">Leurus larryi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the protibial spur antero-dorsally with comb and postero-dorsally with velum (vs. protibial spur antero-dorsally without comb and without velum and postero-dorsally with comb in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gauld &amp; Sithole" authorityYear="2002" box="[493,637,1271,1296]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Forrestopius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="281" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[493,637,1271,1296]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="281">Forrestopius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Additionally, the 
<taxonomicName box="[854,1085,1271,1297]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Forrestopius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="281" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[854,998,1271,1296]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="281">Forrestopius</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
that have two mandibular teeth have 14–20 flagellomeres and the species with three teeth have between 26–30 flagellomeres, while 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Alvarado &amp; Palacio" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Gauld &amp; Sithole" baseAuthorityYear="2002" box="[1296,1391,1307,1333]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Leurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="281" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="larryi">
<emphasis box="[1296,1391,1307,1333]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="281">L. larryi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has two mandibular teeth and 30–32 flagellomeres.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
